ihdl -f ihdl_files verilog_design_file

where

ihdl is the executable name for Verilog In

-f directs the executable to read command arguments from an option
file

ihdl_files is a file that contains the Verilog In options including
the -param option. The -param option references the ihdl_parameter
file, which contains the parameter settings. 

verilog_design_file is the Verilog file you want to import.

COMMAND
========
prompt%ihdl -f ihdl_files Struc_Half_adder.v
